{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://github.com/xhnagata/rigor/schemas/evaluation-report.v1.schema.json",
  "title": "Rigor evaluation report v1",
  "description": "A deterministic report joining an evaluation manifest to recorded evidence artifacts. Every field is fully typed and every object is closed (additionalProperties false). Per-accepted-change rates are denominated by accepted changes and are null when unavailable (no accepted changes, an unresolved-plan attempt, or incomplete elapsed coverage), so a partial value never reads as complete or zero. Every count is a non-negative integer and every missing-data field is enumerated. `configuredRelativeCost` is an abstract configured routing weight, never a price, token count, or verified charge. Over-routing and under-routing are reviewable heuristic counts with explicit definitions, never verdicts.",
